    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_AddNewAgency",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to add a new agency record into the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.AgencyDivision",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table within a Microsoft SQL Server database. It performs validation to ensure that the agency does not already exist, inserts the new agency data, updates the agency hierarchy, and associates the agency with a funding group. The procedure also returns a status code indicating the success of the operation."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple steps, including validation, insertion, hierarchy management, and calling another stored procedure. It handles conditional logic and uses dynamic SQL constructs like "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SCOPE_IDENTITY()",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and joins, which add to its complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
